### Conveniently register schema metadata using .register() method

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/v4/index.mdx

Shows an alternative, more convenient way to add metadata to a schema registry using the `.register()` method directly on the schema. Unlike most Zod methods, `.register()` modifies the schema in place and returns the same schema instance, streamlining metadata assignment.

```ts
emailSchema.register(myRegistry, { title: "Email address", description: "..." })
// => returns emailSchema
```

--------------------------------

### Use the Convenience `.transform()` Method in Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This code demonstrates the `.transform()` convenience method available directly on Zod schemas, which is a shortcut for piping a schema into a transform. This simplifies the syntax for common transformation patterns after validation.

```TypeScript
const stringToLength = z.string().transform(val => val.length);
```

--------------------------------

### Register Schema Using .register() Method (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/metadata.mdx

Explains how to use the `.register()` method directly on a Zod schema to conveniently add it to a specified registry along with its metadata. This method returns the original schema instance, allowing for method chaining.

```ts
const mySchema = z.string();

mySchema.register(myRegistry, { description: "A cool schema!" });
// => mySchema
```

--------------------------------

### Compare Schema Definition for Optional and Nullable Types in Zod vs. Zod Mini

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/packages/mini.mdx

Illustrates the difference in defining optional and nullable string schemas between regular Zod's chained methods and Zod Mini's functional API, highlighting the shift from method chaining to nested function calls.

```ts
// regular Zod
const mySchema = z.string().optional().nullable();
```

```ts
// Zod Mini
const mySchema = z.nullable(z.optional(z.string()));
```

--------------------------------

### Extract Parameter and Return Type Schemas from Function Schema in Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Use .parameters() and .returnType() methods to extract the input and output schemas from a function schema. Returns a ZodTuple for parameters and the return type schema respectively.

```typescript
myFunction.parameters();
// => ZodTuple<[ZodString, ZodNumber]>

myFunction.returnType();
// => ZodBoolean
```

