### Create Zod Array Schema with `array` Method

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Shows how to easily create an array schema for any given Zod type using the `.array()` convenience method. This is a concise way to define an array of a specific type, providing an equivalent to `z.array(z.string())`.

```ts
const stringArray = z.string().array(); // string[]

// equivalent to
z.array(z.string());
```

--------------------------------

### Create Zod Promise Schema with `promise` Method

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Demonstrates how to create a Zod schema for a Promise type using the `.promise()` convenience method. This defines a schema that expects a Promise resolving to the specified type, providing an equivalent to `z.promise(z.string())`.

```ts
const stringPromise = z.string().promise(); // Promise<string>

// equivalent to
z.promise(z.string());
```

