### Make All Properties Optional in Zod Schema

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This shows how to transform an existing Zod object schema to make all its properties optional, analogous to TypeScript's `Partial` utility type. It includes examples for both calling the method directly on the schema and using a utility function.

```typescript
const PartialRecipe = Recipe.partial();
// { title?: string | undefined; description?: string | undefined; ingredients?: string[] | undefined }
```

```typescript
const PartialRecipe = z.partial(Recipe);
// { title?: string | undefined; description?: string | undefined; ingredients?: string[] | undefined }
```

