### Parse data with .parse() method

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

The .parse() method validates data against a Zod schema and returns the value with full type information if valid, or throws an error if invalid. The returned value is a deep clone of the input.

```typescript
const stringSchema = z.string();

stringSchema.parse("fish"); // => returns "fish"
stringSchema.parse(12); // throws error
```

