### Constrain Zod Set Size with min, max, and size Methods (Zod 3)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This example demonstrates how to apply size constraints to a Zod Set schema using direct methods like `min()`, `max()`, and `size()` in Zod 3. These methods ensure the set contains a specific number of items.

```typescript
z.set(z.string()).min(5); // must contain 5 or more items
z.set(z.string()).max(5); // must contain 5 or fewer items
z.set(z.string()).size(5); // must contain 5 items exactly
```

--------------------------------

### Implement Zod-Validated Function with Automatic Validation

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This example shows how to use the `.implement()` method on a Zod function schema. It accepts a function, providing automatic type inference for inputs, and returns a new function that automatically validates its arguments and return values according to the schema.

```ts
const computeTrimmedLength = MyFunction.implement((input) => {
  // TypeScript knows input is a string!
  return input.trim().length;
});

computeTrimmedLength("sandwich"); // => 8
computeTrimmedLength(" asdf "); // => 4
```

--------------------------------

### Define a Prefault Value with Zod .prefault() (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

Illustrates Zod's `.prefault()` method, which parses an `undefined` input using the prefault value without short-circuiting. The prefault value must be assignable to the schema's input type.

```typescript
z.string().transform(val => val.length).prefault("tuna");
schema.parse(undefined); // => 4
```

