### Define and Validate String Schemas with Zod

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs-v3/README.md

Learn how to create a basic string schema using `z.string()`. This example demonstrates both throwing `parse()` and non-throwing `safeParse()` methods for validating input data against the schema.

```ts
import { z } from "zod";

// creating a schema for strings
const mySchema = z.string();

// parsing
mySchema.parse("tuna"); // => "tuna"
mySchema.parse(12); // => throws ZodError

// "safe" parsing (doesn't throw error if validation fails)
mySchema.safeParse("tuna"); // => { success: true; data: "tuna" }
mySchema.safeParse(12); // => { success: false; error: ZodError }
```

--------------------------------

### Make Specific Properties Optional in Zod Schema

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to selectively make certain properties of an existing Zod object schema optional. It covers both the direct method on the schema instance and a utility function, allowing fine-grained control over optionality.

```typescript
const RecipeOptionalIngredients = Recipe.partial({
  ingredients: true,
});
// { title: string; description?: string | undefined; ingredients?: string[] | undefined }
```

```typescript
const RecipeOptionalIngredients = z.partial(Recipe, {
  ingredients: true,
});
// { title: string; description?: string | undefined; ingredients?: string[] | undefined }
```

--------------------------------

### Incorrect Schema Type Inference in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/library-authors.mdx

This example illustrates a common mistake when defining generic functions for Zod schemas. By extending `z4.$ZodType<T>`, the specific subclass type information (e.g., `ZodString`) is lost, limiting the ability to call subclass-specific methods on the returned schema.

```typescript
import * as z4 from "zod/v4/core";

function inferSchema<T>(schema: z4.$ZodType<T>) {
  return schema;
}
```

--------------------------------

### Pick Specific Keys from Zod Object Schema

Source: https://github.com/colinhacks/zod/blob/main/packages/docs/content/api.mdx

This demonstrates how to create a new Zod schema that includes only a subset of keys from an existing object schema, similar to TypeScript's `Pick` utility type. It showcases both the direct method on the schema object and a utility function approach for picking properties.

```typescript
const JustTheTitle = Recipe.pick({ title: true });
```

```typescript
const JustTheTitle = z.pick(Recipe, { title: true });
```
